  "text": "Analytical study of hexagonal plasmonic lens. To validate our FDTD results, we have theoretically calculated the E-field intensity, as well as the phase of the output beam from HPL. All succeeding theoretical calculations have been made for near field, i.e. on the device surface, for simplicity. For a circular plasmonic lens (CPL), the equation of a plasmonic field at an observation point (ρ, θ) due to the excitation along an incremental length of a slit is given by [CITATION_1] : Starting from the inscribed circle in Fig. 5 , we obtain the SPP electric field equations for a circular plasmonic lens (CPL), and modify it to an HPL equation by applying geometric constraints elaborated in Fig. 5 . Consider the amplitude and phase profiles- The positive and negative signs correspond to LCP and RCP incidence, respectively. In case of circular polarization, the dipole sources are aligned parallel to the radius, hence -",
